race.comment: FLYING IMPALA (4) set to peak fourth-up and can return to form quickly. Had no luck in the run from the wide draw when a fading ninth over 1000m at Randwick in Highway class. Blinkers come off and gets a much better set-up for this. Top-three player. LAMBAY (2) had to take his medicine from the wide gate when going back and finishing twelfth over 1400m at Randwick in Highway class. Earlier runs had merit and will be strong late. STAR OF IDA (12) back from a lengthy break with a solid fresh record. Finished fourth in a jump out at Wodonga over 800m recently. Will roll forward from the inside barrier and prove hard to get past. DIVAZOU (8) first blemish of the campaign when a tiring sixth over 1175m at Albury. Maps well and assess on the convincing win two starts back.
